title: 1912 Wisconsin gubernatorial election
text:
The 1912 Wisconsin gubernatorial election was held on November 5, 1912.
Incumbent <a href="Republican%20Party%20%28United%20States%29">Republican</a> <a href="Governor%20of%20Wisconsin">Governor</a> <a href="Francis%20E.%20McGovern">Francis E. McGovern</a> defeated <a href="Democratic%20Party%20%28United%20States%29">Democratic</a> nominee <a href="John%20C.%20Karel">John C. Karel</a> and <a href="Socialist%20Party%20of%20America">Socialist</a> nominee <a href="Carl%20D.%20Thompson">Carl D. Thompson</a>, with 45.55% of the vote.
Primary elections.
<a href="Primary%20election">Primary election</a>s were held on September 3, 1912.
